## AGENTS.md Managed Update Follow-Up

Goal: make the Main Sequence agent scaffold entrypoint marker-managed after migration.
Projects with an unmarked `AGENTS.md` are treated as legacy/unmanaged and are replaced
with the current bootstrap.

Non-goal:

- Do not add a destructive `mainsequence project update AGENTS.md --force` path.
- Do not insert the new managed block into unmarked legacy `AGENTS.md` content.

### Tasks

- [x] Define the managed block contract for Main Sequence scaffold content.
  - Use explicit start/end markers.
  - Include a scaffold version or source marker that can be updated idempotently.
  - Keep the block short: route agents to `.agents/skills/project_builder/SKILL.md`
    and the relevant domain skills instead of embedding full scaffold instructions.

- [x] Add a helper that renders the current managed `AGENTS.md` block from the installed
      `agent_scaffold` bundle metadata.
  - The helper should not read or mutate the project `AGENTS.md`.
  - The helper should produce deterministic text for stable tests.

- [x] Add a helper that updates only the managed block in an existing `AGENTS.md`.
  - If no file exists, create a small starter `AGENTS.md` containing the managed block.
  - If a file exists and has no managed block, replace the whole file with the starter.
  - If a file exists and has a managed block, replace only that block.
  - If markers are malformed or duplicated, fail with a clear message instead of guessing.

- [x] Change `mainsequence project update AGENTS.md` to use the managed-block helper.
  - Preserve the existing project resolution behavior.
  - Preserve the installed bundle resolution behavior.
  - Report whether the file was created, replaced, updated, or unchanged.

